headline: Lowe’s Profit Tops Estimates on Online Growth, Sales to Pros
summary: Adjusted earnings per share were $3.06 in the third quarter, the company said in a statement Wednesday, compared with the $3.00 estimate of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  It saw “continued growth” in sales to professional contractors, a market it has sought to expand in recently.  On Tuesday, Lowe’s larger peer Home Depot Inc. cuts its full-year profit target as consumers pulled back on bigger ticket purchases.

headline: Review & Preview: Risky Business
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 499 points, or 1.1%, while the Nasdaq Composite closed down 1.2%.  “Stocks are suffering losses for the fourth consecutive day as Wall Street adopts a risk-off posture, considering valuation worries, household spending anxiety, employment angst, and elevated inflation that is keeping the Fed at bay and increasingly preventing it from intervening,” writes José Torres, senior economist at Interactive Brokers.  Torres notes that investors spent the day bailing out of the market ahead of tomorrow’s earnings report from Nvidia, as the AI skepticism theme gains traction.
